modules.description: Splits a string into a list of substrings based on a specified Unicode codepoint. It processes UTF-8 encoded strings and returns a list of string fragments. Used to tokenize input streams or parse structured text data.

Splits a UTF-8 encoded OCaml string into a list of individual Unicode code points as separate strings. Operates on standard OCaml strings and leverages the Uutf module for proper Unicode handling. Used to process text for character-level analysis or transformation in multilingual applications.
